ng%20without%20a%20chief%20for%2056%20months%20and%20another%20officer%20has%20been%20made%20acting%20commissioner%2C%20though%20no%20such%20provision%20exists%20in%20the%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChhattisgarh%20has%20been%20functioning%20without%20a%20chief%20since%20December%202022%2C%20Maharashtra%20since%20April%20this%20year%2C%20Bihar%20since%20May%20and%20Punjab%20has%20been%20without%20a%20chief%20information%20commissioner%20since%20last%20month.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnjali%20Bhardwaj%20from%20the%20SNS%2C%20who%20was%20a%20key%20person%20in%20compiling%20the%20report%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20consistent%20behaviour%20of%20the%20government%20we%20have%20seen%20since%202014%20is%20no%20information%20commissioner%20is%20ever%20appointed%20till%20civil%20society%20moves%20%5Bthe%20courts%5D.%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20at%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20direction%20that%20the%20government%20is%20forced%20to%20move.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmrita%20Johri%2C%20also%20of%20the%20SNS%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20good%20way%20to%20crush%20the%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20right%20to%20information%20is%20by%20making%20information%20commissions%20defunct.%20With%20no%20one%20to%20appeal%20to%2C%20an%20application%20for%20information%20gathers%20dust%20till%20it%20has%20no%20meaning%20left.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20Congress%20regime%20%5Balso%5D%20tried%20to%20dilute%20the%20Act%2C%20it%20refrained%20following%20backlash%20from%20civil%20society.%20The%20present%20government%20has%20amended%20the%20Act%20twice%2C%20first%20in%202019%20and%20the%20second%20this%20year%20through%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act.%20Each%20time%2C%20the%20RTI%20Act%20has%20got%20only%20weaker.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20tenure%2C%20salary%20and%20pension%20of%20information%20commissioners%20were%20envisaged%20and%20written%20down%20clearly%20in%20the%20original%20Act.%20In%202019%2C%20this%20was%20amended.%20From%20a%20five-year%20tenure%20and%20a%20salary%20at%20par%20with%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20the%20Act%20now%20says%20these%20are%20conditions%20that%20the%20Centre%20will%20decide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-right-to-information-is-dead-here-is-its-obituary%5C%22%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Information%20Is%20Dead.%20Here%20Is%20its%20Obituary.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20an%20information%20commissioner%20who%20was%20appointed%20in%202020%20was%20a%20journalist%20and%20author%20of%20two%20books%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20Uday%20Mahurkar.%20One%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%E2%80%99s%20members%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Choudhary%2C%20pointed%20out%20in%20his%20protest%20note%20that%20Mahurkar%20had%20not%20even%20applied%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20the%20government%20is%20now%20careful%20about%20who%20they%20appoint.%20Sometimes%20their%20own%20appointee%20passes%20an%20order%20to%20make%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20college%20degree%20public.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20government%20knows%20that%20apart%20from%20weakening%20the%20law%2C%20the%20best%20course%20is%20not%20to%20appoint%20anyone%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Johri.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20other%20way%20to%20deny%20information%20is%20to%20keep%20appeals%20pending%2C%20finds%20the%20SNS.%20As%20many%20as%20%E2%80%9C3%2C21%2C537%20appeals%20and%20complaints%20were%20pending%20on%20June%2030%2C%202023%20in%20the%2027%20information%20commissions%2C%20from%20which%20data%20was%20obtained.%20The%20backlog%20of%20appeals%20and%20complaints%20has%20been%20steadily%20increasing%20in%20commissions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%202019%20assessment%20had%20found%20that%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202019%2C%20a%20total%20of%202%2C18%2C347%20appeals%20and%20complaints%20were%20pending%20in%20the%2026%20information%20commissions%20from%20which%20data%20was%20obtained%2C%20which%20climbed%20to%202%2C86%2C325%20as%20of%20June%2030%2C%202021%20and%20then%20crossed%203%20lakh%20as%20of%20June%2030%2C%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CUsing%20the%20average%20monthly%20disposal%20rate%20and%20the%20pendency%20in%20commissions%2C%20the%20time%20it%20would%20take%20for%20an%20appeal%2Fcomplaint%20to%20be%20disposed%20was%20computed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20assessment%20shows%20that%20West%20Bengal%20SIC%20%5Bstate%20information%20commission%5D%20would%20take%20an%20estimated%2024%20years%20%26amp%3B%201%20month%20to%20dispose%20%5Bof%5D%20a%20matter.%20A%20matter%20filed%20on%20July%201%2C%202023%20would%20be%20disposed%20%5Bof%5D%20in%20the%20year%202047%20at%20the%20current%20monthly%20rate%20of%20disposal!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Maharashtra%20SICs%2C%20estimated%20time%20for%20disposal%20is%20more%20than%204%20years%20and%20in%20Odisha%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20more%20than%202%20years.%20The%20assessment%20shows%20that%2010%20commissions%20would%20take%201%20year%20or%20more%20to%20dispose%20%5Bof%5D%20a%20matter.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20goes%20on%20to%20say%20that%20an%20%E2%80%9Canalysis%20of%20penalties%20imposed%20by%20information%20commissions%20shows%20that%20the%20commissions%20did%20not%20impose%20penalties%20in%2091%25%20of%20the%20cases%20where%20penalties%20were%20potentially%20imposable.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20it%20is%20mandatory%20to%20table%20an%20annual%20report%20in%20parliament.%20The%20report%20says%20that%2019%20out%20of%2029%20information%20commissions%20or%2066%25%20in%20all%20have%20not%20published%20their%20annual%20report%20for%202021-22.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697112010000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsatark-nagrik-sangathan-report-card-information-commission-rti%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Satark%20Nagrik%20Sangathan's%20report%20says%20four%20information%20commissions%20are%20defunct%2C%20while%20pendency%20and%20delays%20are%20endemic.%20This%20is%20part%20of%20efforts%20to%20%26quot%3Bcrush%20the%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20right%20to%20information%26quot%3B%2C%20say%20activists.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsatark-nagrik-sangathan-report-card-information-commission-rti%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parineeti-Raghav%20get%20goofy%20in%20new%20Haldi%20pics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697111998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104374096%2Cimgsize-65292.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fparineeti-chopra-gets-goofy-with-raghav-chadha-at-their-haldi-ceremony-see-unseen-pics-inside%2Farticleshow%2F104374187.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104374187.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUnseen%20pictures%20from%20these%20pre-wedding%20celebrations%20have%20become%20a%20sensation%20on%20the%20internet.%20Recently%2C%20a%20new%20pic%20from%20the%20haldi%20ceremony%20emerged%2C%20where%20Parineeti%20was%20being%20goofy%20with%20Raghav%2C%20smearing%20haldi%20on%20him.%20While%20Parineeti%20was%20seen