survey%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20willingness%20to%20entertain%20an%20archaeological%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyan%20Vapi%20Mosque%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Benaras%20and%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsc-grants-centre-till-oct-31-reply-pleas-challenging-places-of-worship-act-8825813%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Echallenge%20to%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%201991%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20For%20a%20while%2C%20it%20seemed%20that%20both%20the%20Gyan%20Vapi%20mosque%20and%20Shahi%20Idgah%20would%20go%20the%20way%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20may%20still%20happen.%20The%20template%20is%20set%20%E2%80%93%20a%20local%20dispute%20elevated%20to%20a%20national%20issue%2C%20a%20self-appointed%20next%20friend%20of%20the%20idol%2C%20a%20court-mandated%20archaeological%20survey%2C%20and%20a%20judiciary%20which%20values%20faiths%20differentially.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20argued%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Flitigation%2Fsupreme-court-permits-asi-survey-gyanvapi-mosque-premises%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eascertaining%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20a%20place%20was%20not%20barred%20under%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20agreed%20to%20examine%20the%20Act%20itself%2C%20he%20reneged%20directly%20on%20a%20commitment%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20made%20barely%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20In%20an%20otherwise%20disappointing%20judgement%2C%20handing%20over%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20to%20the%20very%20people%20who%20vandalised%20it%2C%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20court%20reiterated%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-places-of-worship-act%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPlaces%20of%20Worship%20Act%20of%201991%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20providing%20a%20guarantee%20for%20the%20preservation%20of%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20places%20of%20public%20worship%20as%20they%20existed%20on%2015%20August%201947%20and%20against%20the%20conversion%20of%20places%20of%20public%20worship%2C%20Parliament%20determined%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3Eindependence%20from%20colonial%20rule%20furnishes%20a%20constitutional%20basis%20for%20healing%20the%20injustices%20of%20the%20past%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20providing%20the%20confidence%20to%20every%20religious%20community%20that%20their%20places%20of%20worship%20will%20be%20preserved%20and%20that%20their%20character%20will%20not%20be%20altered.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20law%20addresses%20itself%20to%20the%20State%20as%20much%20as%20to%20every%20citizen%20of%20the%20nation.%20Its%20norms%20bind%20those%20who%20govern%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20nation%20at%20every%20level%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Those%20norms%20implement%20the%20Fundamental%20Duties%20under%20Article%2051A%20and%20are%20hence%20positive%20mandates%20to%20every%20citizen%20as%20well.%20The%20State%2C%20has%20by%20enacting%20the%20law%2C%20enforced%20a%20constitutional%20commitment%20and%20operationalized%20its%20constitutional%20obligations%20to%20uphold%20the%20equality%20of%20all%20religions%20and%20secularism%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3Ebasic%20featuresof%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20imposes%20a%20non-derogable%20obligation%20towards%20enforcing%20our%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20under%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20law%20is%20hence%20a%20legislative%20instrument%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20secular%20features%20of%20the%20Indian%20polity%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Non-retrogression%20is%20a%20foundational%20feature%20of%20the%20fundamental%20constitutional%20principles%20of%20which%20secularism%20is%20a%20core%20component.%20The%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20is%20thus%20a%20legislative%20intervention%20which%20preserves%20non-retrogression%20as%20an%20essential%20feature%20of%20our%20secular%20values.%E2%80%9D%20%5BE%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emphasis%20supplied%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cnorms%20bind%20those%20who%20govern%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20nation%20at%20every%20level%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20presumably%20includes%20the%20highest%20judiciary.%C2%A0%20Enabling%20the%20buildup%20to%20a%20demand%20for%20the%20conversion%20of%20the%20Gyan%20Vapi%20Mosque%20or%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%2C%20judicially%20or%20otherwise%2C%20should%20really%20be%20classified%20as%20abetment%20under%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%20punishable%20by%20three%20years%20imprisonment%20and%20fine.%20But%20who%20will%20jail%20the%20judges%20and%20who%20will%20bind%20them%20to%20obey%20their%20own%20stated%20norms%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%20politician%20and%20serial%20PIL%20petitioner%20Ashwini%20Upadhyay%E2%80%99s%20challenge%20to%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20rests%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20by%20making%201947%20the%20cut-off%20date%20on%20which%20all%20claims%20to%20restoration%20of%20places%20of%20worship%20would%20cease%2C%20it%20bars%20judicial%20redress%3B%20and%20that%20destroyed%20temples%20are%20really%20still%20temples%20and%20%E2%80%98restoring%E2%80%99%20them%20would%20not%20involve%20conversion.%20The%20same%20argument%20was%20invoked%20in%20the%20Shahi%20Idgah%20petition%20now%20dismissed%20by%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court.%20This%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Eghar%20wapsi%3C%2Fem%3E%20argument%2C%20used%20to%20escape%20culpability%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Hindu%20conversions%20of%20Adivasis%2C%20now%20being%20applied%20to%20Hindu%20temples.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUpadhyay%E2%80%99s%20petition%20is%20deeply%20offensive%20with%20its%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%98Hindus%2C%20Jains%2C%20Buddhists%20and%20Sikhs%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20only%20victims%2C%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%98fundamental%20barbaric%20invaders%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20argument%20that%201192%20(Ghurid%20invasion)%20should%20be%20the%20cut-off%20date%20rather%20than%201947%20for%20restoration%20of%20places%20of%20worship.%20A%20self-respecting%20constitutional%20court%20%E2%80%93%20which%20owes%20its%20very%20existence%20to%20independence%20in%201947%20and%20the%20Republic%20it%20enshrined%20%E2%80%93%20should%20have%20thrown%20out%20the%20petition%20on%20this%20ground%20alone.%20One%20might%20also%20ask%20why%201192%3F%20Why%20not%20go%20back%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F906684%2Fcan-the-arrival-of-the-aryans-in-india-explain-the-disconnect-between-harappan-and-vedic-culture%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eadvent%20of%20the%20Aryans%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintentional%E2%80%9D%20damage%20and%20smashing%20of%20Harappan%20sites%20of%20worship%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20as%20detailed%20by%20the%20archaeologist%20R.S.%20Bisht%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F27164253%2FFRGByCRUYAIbXfO.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F27164253%2FFRGByCRUYAIbXfO.jpeg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F27164253%2FFRGByCRUYAIbXfO-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-642075%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22668%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAshwini%20Upadhyay.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40AshwiniBJP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20three%20issues%20at%20stake%20here%3A%20the%20conception%20of%20history%20that%20is%20being%20enshrined%20in%20the%20courts%20through%20such%20cases%3B%20the%20question%20of%20faith%3B%20and%20the%20question%20of%20who%20is%20entitled%20to%20judicial%20redress%20and%20how.%20But%20before%20that%2C%20it%20would%20be%20useful%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20debates%20on%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESeptember%209%20and%2010%2C%201991%2C%20which%20make%20fascinating%20reading.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EParliamentary%20debates%20on%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Bill%20was%20brought%20in%20as%20part%20of%20a%20commitment%20made%20in%20the%20Congress%20manifesto%2C%20as%20a%20response%20to%20the%20communal%20buildup%20created%20by%20L.K.%20Advani%E2%80%99s%20Rath%20Yatra%2C%20and%20the%20purchase%20of%20land%20by%20the%20Kalyan%20Singh%20government%20next%20to%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20The%20Act%20prescribes%201947%20as%20the%20cutoff%20date%20to%20maintain%20status%20quo%20for%20all%20places%20of%20worship%2C%20abates%20all%20existing%20disputes%20as%20of%20this%20date%3B%20makes%20an%20exception%20for%20the%20Ramjanmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%2C%20buildings%20under%20ASI%20governance%20and%20cases%20settled%20by%20mutual%20acquiescence%20or%20judicial%20decree%20prior%20to%20the%20Act%2C%20and%20prescribes%20a%20punishment%20of%20up%20to%20three%20years%20and%20a%20fine%2C%20for%20any%20kind%20of%20involvement%20in%20converting%20a%20religious%20shrine%20to%20that%20of%20another%20faith%20or%20denomination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20this%20was%20not%20the%20first%20time%20this%20principle%20was%20asserted.%20The%20religious%20sites%20of%20another%20faith%2C%20like%20the%20women%20of%20a%20community%2C%20have%20always%20been%20among%20the%20first%20objects%20of%20attack%20in%20a%20communal%20riot.%20As%20Anil%20Nauria%20has%20pointed%20out%2C%20at%20the%201924%20Unity%20Conference%2C%20following%20riots%20in%20Delhi%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EResolution%20on%20Religious%20Toleration%E2%80%99%20passed%20on%20October%202%2C%201924%20stated%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20all%20places%20of%20worship%2C%20of%20whatever%20faith%20or%20religion%2C%20shall%20be%20considered%20sacred%20and%20inviolable%2C%20and%20shall%20on%20no%20account%20be%20attacked%20or%20desecrated%2C%20whether%20as%20a%20result%20of%20provocation%20or%20by%20way%20of%20retaliation%20for%20sacrilege%20of%20the%20same%20nature.%20It%20shall%20be%20the%20duty%20of%20every%20citizen%20of%20whatever%20faith%20or%20religion%2C%20to%20prevent%20such%20attack%20or%20desecration%20as%20far%20as%20possible%20and%20where%20such%20attack%20or%20desecration%20has%20taken%20place%2C%20it%20shall%20always%20be%20promptly%20condemned.%E2%80%9D%20%5B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Annual%20Register%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%201924%20(Vol%202)%2C%20p.%20156%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%5D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAgain%2C%20after%20the%20illegal%20installation%20of%20the%20Ram%20Lalla%20idol%20inside%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201949%2C%20Pandit%20Sunderlal%20organised%20a%20Qaumi%20Ekta%20Sammelan%20(Religious%20Unity%20Convention)%20in%201950%2C%20in%20which%20Acharya%20Narendra%20Dev%20passed%20a%20resolution%20defending%20status%20quo%20in%20respect%20of%20all%20places%20of%20worship%20from%201947.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%201991%20debate%20over%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20was%20marked%20by%20some%20drama.%20Even%20before%20it%20was%20presented%2C%20BJP%20members%20objected%3B%20they%20frequently%20interrupted%20MPs%20speaking%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20threw%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20wrapper%20at%20one%20MP%2C%20threatened%20to%20%E2%80%9Csee%20people%20outside%20the%20house%E2%80%9D%20and%20finally%20walked%20out.%20BJP%20MPs%20insisted%20that%20the%20Bill%20was%20not%20going%20to%20settle%20disputes%3B%20demanded%20that%20the%20Kashi%20Gyan%20Vapi%20mosque%20and%20Mathura%20Idgah%20also%20be%20excluded%20along%20with%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%3B%20and%20asked%20why%20the%20Bill%20would%20not%20be%20applicable%20to%20J%26amp%3BK.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUma%20Bharti%20asserted%20that%20she%20felt%20wounded%20and%20inferior%20when%20she%20saw%20a%20mosque%20next%20to%20a%20temple.%20Mani%20Shankar%20Iyer%20countered%20this%20by%20saying%20that%20for%20him%20the%20same%20image%20created%20pride%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20composite%20heritage.%20Others%20also%20defended%20the%20Bill%20as%20essential%20for%20secularism%2C%20pointing%20out%20the%20Hindus%20had%20destroyed%20Buddhist%20and%20Jain%20shrines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERam%20Vilas%20Paswan%20and%20Somnath%20Chatterjee%20pointed%20to%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20complicity%20in%20opening%20the%20locks%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20While%20the%20BJP%20wanted%20the%20Ramjanmabhoomi%20to%20be%20handed%20over%20not%20by%20the%20courts%2C%20but%20by%20the%20power%20of%20Hindu%20faith%2C%20Congress%20MPs%20called%20for%20a%20speedy%20judicial%20resolution%20to%20the%20issue%20that%20both%20sides%20would%20have%20to%20accept.%20A%20few%20non-Congress%20MPs%2C%20however%2C%20questioned%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20from%20the%20Bill%2C%20given%20that%20it%20was%20the%20immediate%20cause%20of%20action!%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20BJP%20MPs%20questioned%201947%20as%20the%20cut-off%20date%20arguing%20that%20the%20real%20cut-off%20date%20should%20be%20the%2012%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%2C%20but%20other%20MPs%20stoutly%20defended%20August%2015%2C%201947%20because%20that%20was%20the%20date%20on%20which%20a%20new%20future%20was%20forged%20for%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20important%20question%20raised%20by%20some%20Muslim%20MPs%20%E2%80%93%20P.M.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESayeed%2C%20Ebrahim%20Sulaiman%20Sait%20and%20Sultan%20Salahuddin%20Owaisi%20%E2%80%93%20was%20whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20was%20simply%20conversion%20to%20another%20place%20of%20worship%20that%20would%20count%20or%20any%20change%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20place.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20rooted%20in%20the%20experience%20of%20Muslim%20sacred%20spaces%20post-partition.%20As%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIndrajit%20Gupta%20pointed%20out%2C%20several%20mosques%20and%20dargahs%20in%20Punjab%20had%20been%20taken%20over%20for%20residential%20buildings%2C%20cow%20sheds%20and%20other%20such%20purposes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EYunus%20Saleem%20also%20asked%20for%20protection%20to%20tombs%2C%20graveyards%20and%20other%20such%20sites%20which%20were%20not%20strictly%20objects%20of%20worship%2C%20but%20nevertheless%20sacred.%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20a%20BJP%20MP%20objected%20to%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20ever%20giving%20such%20spaces%20back%20to%20Muslims.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20home%20minister%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20clause%204%20(1)%20covered%20this%20by%20providing%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccontinuance%20of%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20a%20place%20of%20worship%20existing%20on%20the%2015th%20day%20of%20August%2C%201947.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20penal%20action%20is%20prescribed%20only%20for%20conversion%20to%20another%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20considers%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20Act%2C%20it%20would%20do%20well%20to%20remember%20that%20it%20represents%20the%20legacy%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%2C%20the%20secular%20principles%20of%20a%20former%20socialist%20leader%20from%20Ayodhya%2C%20Acharya%20Narendra%20Dev%2C%20and%20the%20majority%20view%20of%20an%20earlier%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F04164827%2Fpic_8.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F04164827%2Fpic_8.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F04164827%2Fpic_8-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-471121%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20early%2020th%20century%20archival%20photograph%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20Photo%3A%20British%20Library%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJudicial%20appreciation%20or%20desecration%20of%20history%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20how%20often%20judiciaries%20are%20called%20upon%20to%20exercise%20historical%20judgments%2C%20and%20how%20they%20claim%20expertise%20in%20doing%20so.%20For%20instance%2C%20while%20hearing%20the%20Gyan%20Vapi%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20it%20would%20consider%20the%20ASI%20report%20as%20it%20had%20done%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20case%2C%20%E2%80%98separating%20the%20grain%20from%20the%20chaff%E2%80%99%2C%20even%20as%20it%20discounted%20the%20views%20of%20non-ASI%20professional%20archaeologists.%20In%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgment%2C%20there%20was%20also%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20immediate%20historical%20context%20in%20which%20Ramjanmabhoomi%20became%20an%20issue%20%E2%80%93%20who%20pulled%20the%20mosque%20down%2C%20etc.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20judgment%20ruled%20it%20irrelevant%20(para%20429).%20To%20any%20professional%20historian%2C%20this%20is%20a%20surprising%20omission.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistory%20in%20multicultural%2C%20multi-religious%20and%20ancient%20societies%20like%20India%2C%20is%20a%20complicated%20issue.%20Take%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Gyan%20Vapi%20itself.%20In%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taylorfrancis.com%2Fchapters%2Fedit%2F10.4324%2F9780429397684-4%2Fvishweshwur-temple-gyan-vapi-mosque-madhuri-desai%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eessay%20on%20entangled%20histories%20in%20Benaras%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Madhuri%20Desai%20points%20out%20that%20there%20was%20no%20archaeological%20or%20recorded%20evidence%20of%20a%20Visheshwur%20temple%20before%20the%2015%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century.%20The%20temple%20that%20was%20ordered%20to%20be%20destroyed%20by%20Aurangzeb%20in%201669%20was%20a%20temple%20that%20had%20been%20built%20under%20Mughal%20patronage%20circa%201590.%20Yet%20this%20earlier%20patronage%20is%20forgotten%20by%20the%20Hindu%20right%20and%20only%20the%20destruction%20is%20highlighted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhether%20Aurangzeb%20demolished%20the%20temple%20because%20a%20Hindu%20queen%20from%20Kutch%20was%20dishonoured%20there%20as%20Pattabhi%20Sitrammaya%20reported%20in%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFeathers%20and%20Stones%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20moot%20question%20today.%20What%20is%20more%20important%20is%20that%20in%202022%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fdisrespecting-hindu-deities-abvp-storms-lucknow-university-threatens-professor%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERavi%20Kant%2C%20a%20Hindi%20lecturer%20at%20Lucknow%20University%2C%20was%20attacked%20by%20the%20ABVP%20and%20an%20FIR%20lodged%20against%20him%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20quoting%20from%20Sitarammaya%E2%80%99s%20account.%20Is%20the%20right%20to%20discuss%20history%20now%20going%20to%20be%20limited%20to%20only%20one%20ideology%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsequent%20rebuildings%20of%20the%20temple%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Mosque%20were%20propelled%20by%20Maratha%20politics%2C%20which%20needed%20to%20weaponise%20Hinduism%20as%20part%20of%20their%20anti-imperial%20struggles.%20Even%20later%2C%20as%20ethnographer%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09584935.2023.2188173%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVera%20Lazaretti%20shows%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20pilgrimage%20around%20the%20Jnana%20Vyapi%20well%20and%20maidan%20was%20the%20subject%20of%20much%20litigation%20over%20decades%20by%20the%20Vyas%20family%20trying%20to%20claim%20exclusive%20rights%2C%20and%20it%20is%20this%20local%20dispute%20which%20has%20been%20picked%20up%20and%20magnified%20by%20the%20RSS.%20But%20as%20Lazaretti%20writes%2C%20ironically%20the%20Vyas%20family%20themselves%20have%20been%20displaced%20by%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20corridor%2C%20and%20their%20role%20as%20litigants%20taken%20over%20by%20lawyer%20Vijay%20Shankar%20Rastogi%20as%20the%20new%20%E2%80%9Cnext%20friend%E2%80%9D%20of%20Kashi%20Vishwanath.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EReligious%20desecrations%20as%20conquest%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuslim%20destruction%20of%20Hindu%20shrines%20was%20clearly%20not%20the%20only%20form%20of%20religious%20destruction.%20Fight%20between%20Shaivites%20and%20Vaishnavites%2C%20between%20different%20denominations%20within%20Christianity%20and%20Islam%20%E2%80%93%20all%20led%20to%20destruction%20of%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20place%20of%20worship.%20Richard%20Davis%20shows%20how%20the%20taking%20of%20idols%20or%20images%20from%20subjugated%20rulers%20and%20placing%20them%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20buildings%20was%20a%20routine%20act%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threeessays.com%2Fproduct%2Fdemolishing-myths-or-mosques-and-temples-readings-on-history-and-temple-desecration-in-medieval-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eindeed%20one%20that%20was%20sanctified%20by%20Manu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20By%20contrast%2C%20temple%20desecration%20was%20more%20limited%2C%20but%20there%20too%2C%20it%20was%20done%20by%20rulers%20as%20part%20of%20conquest%3B%20precisely%20because%20temples%20were%20political%20symbols%2C%20with%20the%20tutelary%20deity%20expressing%20the%20sovereignty%20of%20both%20the%20God%20and%20King.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threeessays.com%2Fproduct%2Fdemolishing-myths-or-mosques-and-temples-readings-on-history-and-temple-desecration-in-medieval-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERichard%20Eaton%20provides%20an%20illustrative%20list%20of%20instances%20where%20Hindu%20kings%20destroyed%20temples%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20A.D.%20642%2C%20according%20to%20local%20tradition%2C%20the%20Pallava%20king%2C%20Narasimhavarman%20I%2C%20looted%20the%20image%20of%20Ganesha%20from%20the%20Chalukyan%20capital%20of%20Vatapi.%20Fifty%20years%20later%2C%20armies%20of%20those%20same%20Chalukyas%20invaded%20North%20India%20and%20brought%20back%20to%20the%20Deccan%20what%20appear%20to%20be%20images%20of%20Ganga%20and%20Yamuna%2C%20looted%20from%20defeated%20powers%20there.%20In%20the%20eighth%20century%2C%20Bengali%20troops%20sought%20revenge%20on%20King%20Lalitaditya%20by%20destroying%20what%20they%20thought%20was%20the%20image%20of%20Vishnu%20Vaikuntha%2C%20the%20state%20deity%20of%20Lalitaditya%E2%80%99s%20kingdom%20in%20Kashmir.%20In%20the%20early%20ninth%20century%2C%20the%20Rashtrakuta%20king%2C%20Govinda%20III%2C%20invaded%20and%20occupied%20Kanchipuram%2C%20which%20so%20intimidated%20the%20king%20of%20Sri%20Lanka%20that%20he%20sent%20Govinda%20several%20(probably%20Buddhist)%20images%20representing%20the%20Sinhala%20state.%20The%20Rashtrakuta%20king%20then%20installed%20these%20in%20a%20Saiva%20temple%20in%20his%20capital.%20About%20the%20same%20time%20the%20Pandyan%20king%2C%20Srimara%20Srivallabha%2C%20also%20invaded%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20took%20back%20to%20his%20capital%20a%20golden%20Buddha%20image-%E2%80%9D%20a%20synecdoche%20for%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20Sinhalese%20polity%20itself%20%E2%80%9C-that%20had%20been%20installed%20in%20the%20kingdom%E2%80%99s%20jewel%20palace.%20In%20the%20early%20tenth%20century%2C%20the%20Pratihara%20king%2C%20Herambapala%2C%20seized%20a%20solid%20gold%20image%20of%20Vishnu%20Vaikuntha%20when%20he%20defeated%20the%20Sahi%20king%20of%20Kangra.%20A%20few%20years%20later%2C%20the%20same%20image%20was%20seized%20from%20the%20Pratiharas%20by%20the%20Candella%20king%2C%20Yasovarman%2C%20and%20installed%20in%20the%20Lakshmana%20temple%20of%20Khajuraho.%20In%20the%20early%20eleventh%20century%2C%20the%20Chola%20king%2C%20Rajendra%20I%2C%20furnished%20his%20capital%20with%20images%20he%20had%20seized%20from%20several%20prominent%20neighboring%20kings%3A%20Durga%20and%20Ganesha%20images%20from%20the%20Chalukyas%3B%20Bhairava%2C%20Bhairavi%2C%20and%20Kali%20images%20from%20the%20Kalingas%20of%20Orissa%3B%20a%20Nandi%20image%20from%20the%20Eastern%20Chalukyas%3B%20and%20a%20bronze%20Siva%20image%20from%20the%20Palas%20of%20Bengal.%20In%20the%20mid-eleventh%20century%2C%20the%20Chola%20king%2C%20Rajadhiraja%2C%20defeated%20the%20Chalukyas%20and%20plundered%20Kalyani%2C%20taking%20a%20large%20black%20stone%20door%20guardian%20to%20his%20capital%20in%20Thanjavur%2C%20where%20it%20was%20displayed%20to%20his%20subjects%20as%20a%20trophy%20of%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20dominant%20pattern%20here%20was%20one%20of%20looting%20royal%20temples%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20carrying%20off%20images%20of%20state%20deities%2C%C2%A0%20we%20also%20hear%20of%20Hindu%20kings%20destroying%20the%20royal%20temples%20of%20their%20political%20adversaries.%20In%20the%20early%20tenth%20century%2C%20the%20Rashtrakuta%20monarch%2C%20Indra%20III%2C%20not%20only%20destroyed%20the%20temple%20of%20Kalapriya%20(at%20Kalpa%20near%20the%20Jamuna%20River)%2C%20patronized%20by%20the%20Rashtrakutas%E2%80%99%20deadly%20enemies%2C%20the%20Pratiharas%2C%20but%20they%20took%20special%20delight%20in%20recording%20the%20fact.%E2%80%9D%20(Eaton%2C%20%3Cem%3ETemple%20Desecration%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20pg%20105)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%2C%20therefore%2C%20nothing%20unique%20about%20Muslim%20rulers%20destroying%20temples.%20Why%20do%20RSS%20petitions%20never%20use%20the%20same%20language%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbarbaric%20invaders%E2%80%9D%20against%20these%20Hindu%20medieval%20kings%3F%20The%20figures%20of%20temple%20destructions%20are%20also%20significantly%20lower%20than%20is%20claimed%20by%20the%20Hindutva%20believers.%20Moreover%2C%20temple%20destruction%2C%20when%20it%20did%20occur%2C%20was%20directed%20by%20rulers%20at%20temples%20associated%20intimately%20with%20other%20rulers%2C%20and%20not%20by%20ordinary%20Muslims%20or%20Hindus.%20Compare%20this%20to%20the%20present%2C%20when%20every%20Hindutva%20ideologue%20feels%20entitled%20to%20punish%20every%20ordinary%20Muslim.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHindu%20replacement%20of%20Buddhist%20shrines%20is%20a%20widespread%20phenomenon%2C%20and%20not%20all%20of%20this%20was%20peaceful.%20Caves%2014%20and%2015%20of%20the%20Ellora%20caves%20were%20originally%20Buddhist%20viharas%20which%20were%20then%20converted%20to%20Hindu%20shrines.%20It%20now%20emerges%20from%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fhc-verdict-on-thalaivetti-muniyappan-opens-up-space-for-buddhist-history-in-state%2Farticle65775967.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMadras%20high%20court%20order%20of%202022%20that%20the%20idol%20of%20Thalaivetti%20Muniyappan%20in%20Salem%20was%20actually%20a%20statue%20of%20the%20Buddha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20court%20has%20ordered%20the%20land%20of%20the%20temple%20to%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Archaeology%20department%20and%20for%20Hindu%20rituals%20to%20cease.%20In%20an%20equal%20world%2C%20accepting%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20would%20throw%20up%20a%20legal%20tsunami.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20place%20may%20change%20hands%20between%20multiple%20faiths%20in%20its%20history%20%E2%80%93%20for%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20Daulatbad%20fort%2C%20a%20Jain%20temple%20was%20converted%20to%20a%20Muslim%20mosque%20and%20then%20converted%20to%20a%20Bharat%20Mata%20temple.%20Should%20it%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Jains%20or%20the%20Muslims%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReligious%20desecration%20as%20conquest%2C%20is%2C%20however%2C%20not%20the%20only%20reason%20why%20religious%20places%20may%20lose%20their%20original%20character.%20Populations%20die%20out%20in%20a%20particular%20place%2C%20shrines%20acquire%20new%20worshippers%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20glorious%20examples%20in%20this%20country%20of%20syncretism%20where%20people%20of%20diverse%20faiths%20worship%20together%20as%20in%20the%20Sufi%20dargahs%20of%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorical%20and%20religious%20structures%20are%20inevitably%20layered%20upon%20each%20other%2C%20and%20a%20petition%20which%20seeks%20to%20privilege%20one%20kind%20of%20restoration%20of%20a%20place%20of%20worship%20over%20others%20needs%20to%20be%20thrown%20out%20at%20the%20very%20outset%20as%20violative%20of%20Article%2014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17131029%2F2022_5img14_May_2022_PTI05_14_2022_000146B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17131029%2F2022_5img14_May_2022_PTI05_14_2022_000146B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17131029%2F2022_5img14_May_2022_PTI05_14_2022_000146B-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F17131029%2F2022_5img14_May_2022_PTI05_14_2022_000146B-1024x682.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-597052%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Dham%20and%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20complex%2C%20in%20Varanasi.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhen%20the%20state%20demolishes%20Hindu%20temples%2C%20does%20that%20make%20it%20more%20legitimate%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20Hindus%20who%20care%20only%20when%20Muslims%20demolish%20their%20temples%20rather%20than%20when%20the%20government%20does%20so%2C%20in%20the%20name%20of%20development%2C%20road%20widening%2C%20removing%20encroachments%2C%20etc.%20actually%20care%20less%20about%20their%20temples%20and%20their%20religion%20than%20about%20getting%20the%20better%20of%20Muslims.%20The%20best%20example%20perhaps%20is%20the%20destruction%20of%20Shoolpaneshwar%20and%20other%20old%20Shiva%20temples%20along%20the%20Narmada%20which%20is%20itself%20sacred.%20Why%20do%20the%20cracks%20in%20the%20Badrinath%20temple%20and%20the%20sinking%20of%20Joshimath%20due%20to%20reckless%20building%20in%20the%20hills%20not%20excite%20the%20same%20emotions%20both%20among%20ardent%20Hindutva%20adherents%20and%20the%20BJP%20governments%20in%20power%2C%20as%20does%20demolishing%20a%20mosque%20in%20order%20to%20build%20a%20grand%20new%20temple%20there%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Muslim%20shrines%2C%20however%2C%20a%20BJP-run%20government%20is%20almost%20synonymous%20with%20the%20Hindutva%20vigilante%20brigades.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Frioters-raze-ghazal-pioneer-s-tomb%2Fcid%2F898081%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAhmedabad%20Municipal%20Corporation%20building%20a%20road%20over%20Vali%20Guajrati%E2%80%99s%20tomb%20in%20Ahmedabad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20really%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%202002%20pogroms%2C%20in%20which%20mosques%20and%20dargahs%20were%20destroyed.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Union%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fexplained-what-is-the-tussle-between-the-central-government-and-the-delhi-waqf-board%2Farticle67327722.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dbeen%2520touched%2520yet.-%2CThe%2520Union%2520Housing%2520and%2520Urban%2520Affairs%2520Ministry%2520has%2520taken%2520over%2Cthe%2520status%2520of%2520these%2520monuments.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMinistry%E2%80%99s%20takeover%20of%20123%20properties%20belonging%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Waqf%20Board%20and%20the%20demolition%20of%20some%20of%20them%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20name%20of%20road%20widening%20is%20clearly%20malafide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20urban%20beautification%20logic%20which%20is%20applied%20to%20century-old%20mosques%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20matter%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20hundreds%20of%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPracheen%20Shiv%20Mandirs%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPracheen%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHanuman%20Mandirs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20which%20dot%20our%20cities%20in%20North%20India.%20Before%20my%20eyes%2C%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPracheen%20Shiv%20Mandir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20came%20up%20in%20my%20residential%20area%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20next%20to%20a%20board%20which%20said%20%E2%80%98Government%20land%2C%20do%20not%20trespass.%E2%80%99%20The%20police%20sat%20outside%20it%20while%20it%20was%20being%20constructed%20and%20held%20COVID-19%20vaccine%20camps%20there.%20Incidentally%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fshahemardan.org%2Findex.php%3Foption%3Dcom_content%26view%3Darticle%26id%3D1%26Itemid%3D24%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20entire%20area%20used%20to%20be%20a%20Shia%20graveyard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20was%20transformed%20into%20a%20Hindu%20colony%20after%20Partition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUpadhyay%20claims%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Bill%20cuts%20off%20legal%20redress.%20This%20is%20no%20more%20than%20any%20statute%20of%20limitations.%20Instead%2C%20one%20might%20argue%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20enables%20legal%20redress%20for%20people%20whose%20shrines%20have%20been%20forcibly%20taken%20over%20by%20more%20powerful%20forces%2C%20which%20in%20India%20today%2C%20can%20only%20be%20the%20RSS%20followers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAdivasi%20places%20of%20worship%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20all%20the%20communities%20that%20need%20to%20invoke%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20and%20demand%20the%20restoration%20of%20their%20shrines%2C%20it%20is%20the%20Adivasis.%20As%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20vulnerable%20and%20constitutionally%20protected%20groups%2C%20it%20is%20they%20who%20should%20be%20the%20first%20charge%20on%20the%20legal%20system.%20Unfortunately%2C%20however%2C%20their%20beliefs%20are%20totally%20discounted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20hill%20in%20Giridih%20where%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fexplained-why-are-the-adivasis-protesting-against-jain-dominance-in-marang-buru-or-parasnath-news-252378%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThousands%2520of%2520tribals%2520climbed%2520the%2Cand%2520practices%2520in%2520the%2520area.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAdivasis%20worship%20as%20Marang%20Buru%20and%20Jains%20worship%20as%20the%20Parasnath%20hill%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20BJP%20government%20wanted%20to%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20tourist%20spot%2C%20and%20backed%20off%20only%20under%20Jain%20protest.%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20hand%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcaravanmagazine.in%2Freligion%2Fpk-sajeev-sabarimala-mala-araya-brahminisation-adivasi-deity%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESabrimalai%20temple%20back%20to%20the%20Mala%20Araya%20tribal%20community%20who%20were%20displaced%20from%20it%20by%20Brahmin%20priests%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%20In%20the%20last%20three%20decades%20alone%2C%20I%20have%20seen%20how%20several%20Adivasi%20and%20OBC%20priests%20have%20been%20displaced%20from%20small%20shrines%20in%20Bastar%2C%20and%20the%20space%20taken%20over%20by%20Brahmins.%20By%20traditional%20accounts%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmagazines.odisha.gov.in%2Forissareview%2F2019%2FJun-July%2Fengpdf%2FJagannath-cult-and-its-linkage-24-31.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELord%20Jagannath%20of%20Puri%20was%20stolen%20from%20the%20Sabaras%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20kind%20of%20religious%20appropriation%20is%20just%20one%20of%20the%20many%20attacks%20that%20are%20taking%20place%20on%20Adivasi%20religious%20sites.%20Sacred%20hills%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Faadc804c-4cd1-3cf2-982c-53d3ccf73c09%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENiyamgiri%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Odisha)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fvideos%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fmaharashtra-tribal-devotees-participate-in-surjagarh-yatra%2Fvideoshow%2F96815428.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESurjagadh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Maharashtra)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fchhattisgarh-locals-protesting-against-rowghat-iron-ore-project-clash-with-police-in-narayanpur%2F898971%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERaoghat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Chhattisgarh)%20are%20being%20taken%20over%20for%20mining%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findependence-mining-gadchiroli-adivasi-protest-maharashtra%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20believers%20who%20worshipped%20at%20these%20shrines%20are%20being%20attacked%20for%20protesting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgment%2C%20the%20court%20emphasised%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epractice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20worship%20in%20determining%20who%20should%20have%20title%20to%20the%20land.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20Adivasi%20sacred%20hills%2C%20there%20is%20evidence%20of%20continued%20practice%20of%20worship%20over%20several%20generations%2C%20with%20people%20coming%20from%20far%20away%2C%20even%20neighbouring%20states.%20Even%20when%20closed%20off%20by%20mining%20authorities%2C%20as%20in%20the%20Bailadilla%20hills%2C%20Adivasis%20seek%20permission%20from%20mining%20authorities%20to%20go%20and%20worship%2C%20because%20it%20would%20be%20inconceivable%20to%20abandon%20that%20sacred%20space.%20As%20of%201947%2C%20they%20were%20places%20of%20worship%20and%20should%20be%20recognised%20as%20such%2C%20even%20if%20a%20postcolonial%20government%20wants%20to%20enact%20colonial%20practices%2C%20treating%20them%20as%20%3Cem%3Eterra%20nullius%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20available%20for%20mining.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMutual%20accords%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20makes%20an%20exception%20for%20places%20of%20worship%20whose%20conversion%20is%20settled%20by%20mutual%20acquiescence%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebefore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20Act.%20Perhaps%20the%20lawmakers%20recognised%20that%20mutual%20acquiescence%20in%20a%20communal%20vitiated%20atmosphere%20where%20one%20side%20was%20dominant%20was%20meaningless.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-dargah-inside-the-complex-pavgadh-temple-harmony-of-faiths-7974241%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edargah%20at%20Pavagadh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20Uma%20Bharti%20claimed%20in%20the%20parliamentary%20debates%20on%20the%20Place%20of%20Worship%20Bill%2C%20hurt%20her%20sentiments%2C%20has%20now%20been%20removed%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmutual%20consent%E2%80%9D%2C%20enabling%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20unfurl%20a%20triumphal%20flag%20atop%20the%20temple%20spire.%20One%20can%20only%20presume%20that%20this%20was%20much%20like%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.onlinevolunteers.org%2Fgujarat%2Freports%2Frural%2Frural-gujarat-04.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecompros%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20that%20enabled%20Muslim%20villagers%20to%20return%20to%20their%20villages%20after%20the%202002%20pogroms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20perhaps%20all%20is%20not%20lost%20in%20this%20country.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fhindus-sikhs-came-together-punjab-barnala-villages-build-mosques-communal-harmoney-2420122-2023-08-12%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20Sikhs%20of%20Punjab%20have%20restored%20mosques%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20were%20abandoned%20after%20Muslims%20migrated%20to%20Pakistan.%20It%20is%20this%20model%20that%20we%20need%20to%20emulate%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20seeks%20to%20promote%20communal%20harmony%20in%20the%20present%20%E2%80%93%20rather%20than%20the%20revanchist%20and%20illiterate%20model%20promoted%20by%20the%20RSS.%20But%20for%20this%2C%20the%20courts%20must%20respect%20the%20faith%20of%20all%20Indians%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20respect%20the%20constitution%20in%20which%20all%20Indians%20have%20faith.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENandini%20Sundar%20is%20a%20Delhi%20based%20sociologist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pu