%20cost%20and%20lack%20of%20available%20teachers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKentucky%20may%20have%20solved%20both%20issues%20with%20a%20new%20policy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20state%20now%20gives%20free%20tuition%20to%20the%20children%20of%20childcare%20teachers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20in%20a%20full-blown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcost-of-childcare-crisis-get-worse-in-september-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-costs-expensive-rising-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20one%20potential%20solution%20appears%20to%20be%20working%2C%20but%20only%20if%20governments%20are%20willing%20to%20step%20in%20and%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20is%20two-fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20childcare%20is%20expensive.%20Based%20on%20the%20average%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.childcareaware.org%2Fcatalyzing-growth-using-data-to-change-child-care-2022%2F%23PriceofCare%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20cost%20of%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20US%20of%20%2410%2C600%20per%20child%20and%20the%20median%20household%20income%20of%20%2470%2C784%20from%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau%2C%20families%20spend%2015%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20childcare%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20if%20they%20have%20only%20one%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20finding%20openings%20can%20often%20be%20challenging%2C%20even%20if%20you%20can%20afford%20childcare.%20As%20of%202018%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchildcaredeserts.org%2F2018%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20American%20Progress%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20over%20half%20of%20Americans%20lived%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-deserts-labor-shortage-infrastructure-affordable-childcare-working-parents-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20desert%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20the%20number%20of%20children%20outnumbered%20licensed%20care%20slots%20by%20three%20to%20one%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcost-of-childcare-crisis-get-worse-in-september-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20are%20leaving%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20forgoing%20current%20earnings%20and%20potential%20advancement%2C%20to%20stay%20home%20with%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ideal%20solution%20would%20address%20both%20of%20those%20issues%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20and%20Kentucky%20may%20have%20figured%20one%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20possible%20solution%20in%20the%20Bluegrass%20State%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Kentucky%20attempted%20to%20address%20the%20double-whammy%20of%20cost%20and%20lack%20of%20available%20childcare%20by%20making%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyyouth.org%2Fcelebrating-new-benefits-for-child-care-employees%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20free%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20licensed%20and%20certified%20childcare%20program%20employees%2C%20regardless%20of%20household%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F10%2F06%2F1203182131%2Fkentucky-free-child-care-day-care-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20state%20made%20the%20change%20when%20they%20noticed%20the%20number%20of%20children%20receiving%20childcare%20subsidies%20during%20the%20pandemic%20fell%20by%20nearly%20half%20because%20parents%20were%20struggling%20to%20find%20open%20spots%20and%20classrooms%20stood%20empty%20due%20to%20teacher%20shortages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Capitol%20Building%20of%20the%20Commonwealth%20of%20Kentucky%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6526d60855f52b01b35cb6f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECapitol%20Building%20of%20the%20Commonwealth%20of%20Kentucky%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Light%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20was%20exacerbated%20by%20stricter%20pandemic%20child-to-teacher%20ratios%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20struggle%20to%20find%20people%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-costs-expensive-rising-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estaffing%20needs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20centers%20can't%20meet%20staffing%20requirements%20is%20simply%20that%20the%20job%20doesn't%20pay%20well.%20According%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-workers-pay-quit-impact-on-children-tuition-increase-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edaycare%20childcare%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20an%20average%20of%20%2412.40%20an%20hour%2C%20less%20than%20half%20the%20average%20for%20all%20occupations%20(%2428.01).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fchild-care-costs-in-the-united-states%2F%3Fgclid%3DCj0KCQjwla-hBhD7ARIsAM9tQKt6M1mYtQWNuiqliqWxgCF_IA18gNpV6ILXYv4n88mc3t6sXkgMlMMaAiEcEALw_wcB%23%2FKY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEconomic%20Policy%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20the%20families%20of%20childcare%20workers%20are%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20live%20in%20poverty%20(11.8%25)%20compared%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20is%20some%20find%20the%20work%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-workers-quitting-low-pay-childcare-shortage-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ementally%20exhausting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20someone's%20burnt%20out%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%20and%20quit%2C%20and%20there's%20nothing%20you%20can%20do%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Sinead%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20childcare%20worker%20in%20West%20Virginia%20and%20%249.50%20an%20hour%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-workers-pay-quit-impact-on-children-tuition-increase-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BOr%20they%20just%20realize%20they%20can%20make%20a%20higher%20wage%20at%20Walmart%20and%20much%20less%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D99a747535cacce4bae670973a993e82e33ff332ae9e386e4c40474f46fd0d8a8%26postID%3D6526b3c2385cb39deadbac49%26postSlug%3Ddaycare-costs-childcare-workers-kentucky-policy-crisis-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.ziprecruiter.com%252FSalaries%252FWalmart-Stocking-Salary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20ZipRecruiter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20can%20make%20an%20average%20of%20%2417.00%20per%20hour%20stocking%20shelves%20at%20Walmart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKentucky's%20solution%20is%20working%2C%20but%20at%20a%20cost%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKentucky's%20solution%20was%20designed%20to%20help%20parents%20who%20left%20jobs%20to%20avoid%20daycare%20expenses%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20creating%20more%20spots%20for%20other%20parents%20by%20having%20more%20teachers%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20instituting%20the%20new%20subsidies%20for%20center%20employees%2C%20the%20number%20of%20children%20receiving%20state%20subsidies%20more%20than%20doubled%20to%2040%2C000%2C%20including%203%2C600%20children%20of%20staff%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20drops%20a%20child%20off%20at%20preschool.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6526d6606561dd877e77c533%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20woman%20drops%20a%20child%20off%20at%20preschool.%3Cp%3EFly%20View%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20does%20come%20at%20a%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fchild-care-costs-in-the-united-states%2F%3Fgclid%3DCj0KCQjwla-hBhD7ARIsAM9tQKt6M1mYtQWNuiqliqWxgCF_IA18gNpV6ILXYv4n88mc3t6sXkgMlMMaAiEcEALw_wcB%23%2FKY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInfant%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Kentucky%20costs%20an%20average%20of%20%24534%20per%20month.%20If%20you%20have%20two%20children%2C%20it%20is%20about%20%2413%2C000%20per%20year%2C%20or%20approximately%2032%25%20more%20than%20the%20average%20rent%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NPR%2C%20Kentucky%20pays%20the%20center%20as%20much%20as%20%24200%20per%20week%20to%20cover%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20employee's%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENPR%20found%20one%20example%20of%20a%20center%20offering%20free%20tuition%20to%20employees%20without%20state%20assistance%20in%20West%20Virginia.%20The%20move%20helped%20open%20spots%20for%20people%20on%20waiting%20lists%2C%20but%20one%20or%20more%20of%20those%20spots%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20by%20a%20family%20not%20paying%20tuition%2C%20lowering%20the%20center's%20revenue%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCenters%20can't%20afford%20to%20give%20those%20spots%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20daycare%20center%20owner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F10%2F06%2F1203182131%2Fkentucky-free-child-care-day-care-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20waiting%20lists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThings%20are%20more%20dire%20at%20the%20federal%20level%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20childcare%20will%20also%20rise%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-costs-expensive-rising-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20approved%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20that%20ran%20out%20in%20September%20is%20not%20replaced.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naeyc.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fwysiwyg%2Fuser-73607%2Fnovember_2022_naeyc_policy_fieldsurvey_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20for%20the%20Education%20of%20Young%20Children%20found%20that%2043%25%20of%20surveyed%20childcare%20center%20directors%20said%20they%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20raise%20tuition%20when%20funding%20ran%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Many%20childcare%20centers%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20close.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6526d6d16561dd877e77c63b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20childcare%20centers%20may%20be%20forced%20to%20close.%3Cp%3ELuis%20Alvarez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20government%20funding%20ran%20out%2C%20it%20also%20put%20more%20centers%20at%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-costs-expensive-rising-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclosing%20their%20doors%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20snowball%20would%20force%20more%20families%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20work%20or%20quit.%20The%20foundation%20estimated%20the%20cost%20would%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%249%20billion%20in%20earnings%20for%20families.%20That%20would%20be%20on%20top%20of%20the%20%2478%20billion%20parents%20are%20already%20losing%20in%20income%20due%20to%20inadequate%20childcare%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Flack-of-child-care-costs-economy-122-billion-dollars-parents-businesses-taxpayers-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20economist%20Clive%20R.%20Belfield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20needs%20more%20affordable%20daycare%20and%20more%20people%20to%20work%20at%20the%20centers.%20Giving%20workers%20free%20tuition%20for%20their%20children%20can%20work%2C%20but%20only%20with%20government%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaycare-costs-childcare-workers-kentucky-policy-crisis-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697106001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6526d4836561dd877e77bf0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaycare-costs-childcare-workers-kentucky-policy-crisis-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20is%20in%20a%20childcare%20crisis%20due%20to%20cost%20and%20lack%20of%20available%20teachers%2C%20but%20Kentucky%20may%20have%20a%20solution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cgaines%40insider.com%20(Cork%20Gaines)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaycare-costs-childcare-workers-kentucky-policy-crisis-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20you%20were%20thinking%20about%20moving%20to%20Portugal%2C%20it%20just%20got%20a%20whole%20lot%20more%20expensive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lisbon%20portugal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cf91e4411e2053bc0437368%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EESB%20Professional%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPortugal%20is%20ending%20a%20hefty%20tax%20break%20for%20foreigners%20in%202024%20that%20incentivized%20many%20to%20move%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20newcomers%20arrived%20in%20the%20country%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20drove%20up%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20for%20locals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20announcement%20already%20has%20some%20Americans%20reconsidering%20a%20move%20to%20the%20once-affordable%20nation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPortugal%20has%20long%20ranked%20high%20on%20the%20list%20for%20Americans%20looking%20to%20move%20abroad%20because%20of%20its%20affordability.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20its%20golden%20visa%2C%20favorable%20tax%20incentives%20for%20foreigners%2C%20and%20low%20housing%20costs%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-moving-to-portugal-golden-visa-d7-overcrowding-housing-costs-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20became%20a%20major%20destination%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20global%20movers%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20come%202024%2C%20it%20will%20be%20significantly%20more%20expensive%20to%20live%20there%20if%20you're%20coming%20from%20another%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20already%20have%20clients%20that%20are%20looking%20to%20reconsider%20their%20plans%26quot%3B%20to%20move%2C%20Alex%20Ingrim%2C%20a%20private%20wealth%20manager%20at%20Chase%20Buchanan%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnt%C3%B3nio%20Costa%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Portugal%2C%20announced%20that%20the%20country%20is%20scrapping%20its%20non-habitual%20resident%20tax%20regime%20(NHR)%2C%20a%20popular%20tool%20used%20by%20foreigners%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20expenses.%20Now%20those%20moving%20to%20Portugal%20in%202024%20and%20beyond%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20income%20tax%20as%20everyone%20else%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lemonde.fr%2Fen%2Finternational%2Farticle%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fportugal-to-end-tax-scheme-for-foreigners-from-2024_6146323_4.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELe%20Monde%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENHR%20was%20introduced%20in%202009%2C%20after%20the%20Global%20Financial%20Crisis%2C%20to%20attract%20foreign%20talent%20and%20wealth%20to%20the%20country.%20Currently%20foreigners%20who%20are%20accepted%20into%20the%20program%20had%20income%20taxed%20at%20a%20flat%20rate%20of%2020%25%2C%20while%20retirees%20had%20pension%20taxes%20at%2010%25%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.portugal.com%2Fnews%2Fportugals-non-habitual-resident-tax-regime-to-end-in-2024%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIt%2520was%2520introduced%2520in%25202009%2Cthe%2520current%2520conditions%2520are%2520unsustainable.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20Portugal.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20made%20Portugal%20a%20really%20attractive%20jurisdiction%20to%20work%20or%20to%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingrim%20said.%20Foreigners%20%26quot%3Bwere%20also%20tax%20exempt%20on%20capital%20gains%20on%20property%20transactions%20abroad%20or%20rental%20income%20that%20was%20generated%20abroad%2C%20so%20it%20had%20all%20of%20these%20different%20advantages%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lisbon%20portugal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a0ccf7e35876e491e8b62ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221266%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELisbon%2C%20Portugal.%3Cp%3EJose%20Manuel%20Ribeiro%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20to%20reconsider%20why%20they%20were%20moving%20to%20Portugal%20if%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20as%20easy%20as%20they%20first%20thought%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingrim%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClose%20to%2010%2C000%20Americans%20were%20living%20in%20Portugal%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Portuguese%20government%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F03%2F17%2Frealestate%2Feurope-homes-sale-americans-lisbon-barcelona.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBy%25202022%252C%2520nearly%252010%252C000%2520American%2Cprovided%2520by%2520the%2520Portuguese%2520government.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%20of%20239%25%20since%202017.%20As%20foreign%20wealth%20moved%20into%20the%20country%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20skyrocketed.%20Now%2C%20trying%20to%20walk%20back%20the%20success%20of%20the%20programs%20the%20country%20put%20in%20place%20to%20stoke%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20changing%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20points%20of%20attraction%3A%20the%20savings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20advantages%20will%20be%20wiped%20away%20for%20new%20foreign%20residents%20in%202024.%20For%20Portuguese%20residents%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalcitizensolutions.com%2Ftaxes-in-portugal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaxes%20range%20from%2014.5%25%20to%2048%25%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20depending%20on%20what%20you%20earn%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20band%20is%20for%20earners%20bringing%20in%2075%2C010%20euros%20(or%20%2479%2C647)%20a%20year%20or%20more%2C%20according%20to%20investment%20migration%20firm%20Global%20Citizen%20Solutions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20see%20that%20there's%20a%20huge%20difference%20between%20having%20a%2010%25%20flat%20tax%20on%20a%20social%20security%20account%20or%20potentially%20paying%20something%20like%2035%25%2C%2045%25%2C%2048%25%20on%20your%20income%20in%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingrim%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20already%20living%20in%20Portugal%2C%20like%20Dan%20Bagby%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Michelle%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-moving-to-portugal-golden-visa-d7-overcrowding-housing-costs-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewho%20moved%20to%20Lisbon%20from%20Texas%20in%202021%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20won't%20be%20immediately%20affected.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20posing%20for%20a%20picture%20in%20Portugal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646cfa68a739dc0018090e5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22998%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDan%20and%20Michelle%20Bagby%20sold%20their%20house%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas%20and%20moved%20to%20Lisbon%2C%20Portugal%20in%202021.%3Cp%3EHoneymoon%20Always%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20accepted%2C%20NHR's%20perks%20last%20for%2010%20years.%20Bagby%20is%20working%20on%20Portuguese%20citizenship%20and%20told%20Insider%20that%20once%20his%20status%20changes%2C%20his%20taxes%20still%20won't%20until%202031.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20it%20really%20doesn't%20change%20anything%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Bagby%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20about%20seven%20more%20years%20left.%20I'm%20not%20really%20worried%20about%20it%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20arrival%20of%20Americans%20and%20other%20foreigners%20pushed%20the%20country's%20real-estate%20market%20to%20new%20highs.%20House%20prices%20increased%20157%25%20from%202020%20to%202021%2C%20according%20to%20Eurostat%2C%20the%20European%20Union's%20statistics%20agency.%20And%20rents%20rose%20112%25%20from%202015%20to%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fportugal-housing-crisis-lisbon-tourism-6e9e08c136b6dc98bf5cb51292c0f27b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20Associated%20Press%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%20the%20country%20announced%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fportugal-shutting-down-golden-visa-d7-digital-nomad-still-open-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eend%20to%20its%20popular%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20visa%26quot%3B%20program%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20allowed%20investors%20to%20obtain%20residency%20permits%20in%20exchange%20for%20purchasing%20residential%20real%20estate%20worth%20at%20least%20500%2C000%20euros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnding%20NHR%20is%20anticipated%20to%20help%20correct%20the%20housing%20market%20by%20making%20foreign%20buyers%20pay%20their%20fair%20share%20in%20taxes.%20But%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20going%20up%20and%20reaching%20levels%20of%20parity%20with%20other%20countries%2C%20foreigners%20may%20not%20move%20to%20Portugal%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20causing%20people%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%20and%20go%2C%20'Okay%2C%20Portugal%20was%20the%20easy%20answer%20and%20now%20there's%20no%20other%20easy%20answer%20out%20there.%20France%2C%20Italy%20or%20Spain%20might%20be%20back%20on%20the%20table%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ingrim%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-to-portugal-income-taxes-golden-visa-buy-house-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697105761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65270abd68f1d46f52af3745%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-to-portugal-income-taxes-golden-visa-buy-house-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Portugal's%20affordability%20drew%20foreign%20movers%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20the%202024%20ending%20of%20a%20hefty%20tax%20break%20already%20has%20some%20reconsidering.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moving-to-portugal-income-taxes-golden-visa-buy-house-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20Hopes%20to%20Best%20US%20in%20New%20India%20Fighter%20Race%2C%20Betting%20on%20Existing%20Rafale%20Sales%2C%20Tech%20Flexibility%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%