t%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri-Jan%20Arogya%20Yojna%20(PM-JAY)%20insurance%20scheme%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Bajaj%20Allianz%20General%20Insurance%20Company%2C%20on%20December%2026%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20on%20December%2027%2C%202020%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20Chief%20Secretary%20Dr%20Arun%20K.%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20Lakshya%20Mehta%2C%20was%20hired%20by%20the%20insurance%20company%20where%20he%20currently%20serves%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Senior%20Executive%E2%80%99%2C%20according%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20insurance%20company%20sought%20to%20pull%20out%20of%20the%20contract%20in%20September%20next%20year%2C%20the%20SHA%20modified%20the%20contract%20by%20providing%20a%2015%25%20addendum%20to%20the%20existing%20policy%20without%20any%20legal%20backing.%20The%20%E2%80%98illegal%E2%80%99%20changes%20were%20regularised%20by%20the%20Administrative%20Council%20headed%20by%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Sinha%2C%20even%20though%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20finance%20and%20law%20departments%20objected%20to%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20activist%20flagged%20these%20alleged%20irregularities%20to%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigations%2C%20the%20agency%20transferred%20the%20complaint%20after%20six%20months%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Anti-Corruption%20Bureau%20(ACB)%20whose%20director%20reports%20to%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%2C%20one%20of%20the%20alleged%20suspects%20in%20the%20purported%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20claims%20are%20part%20of%20a%20letter%20by%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Public%20Enterprises%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20and%201992%20IAS%20officer%2C%20Ashok%20Kumar%20Parmar%2C%20to%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigations.%20The%20letter%20seeks%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeeper%20probe%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Insurance%20Regulatory%20and%20Development%20Authority%20of%20India%20(IRDA)%20and%20the%20CBI%20into%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjk-top-ias-officer-ashok-kumar-parmar-cbi-probe-jal-jeevan-mission%5C%22%3EJ%26amp%3BK%3A%20Why%20a%20Top%20IAS%20Officer%20Has%20Sought%20a%20CBI%20Probe%20Into%20the%20Flagship%20Jal%20Jeevan%20Mission%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EParmar%2C%20who%20previously%20flagged%20the%20alleged%20irregularities%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20Jal%20Jeevan%20Mission%2C%20a%20centrally-sponsored%20scheme%2C%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20has%20also%20sought%20protection%20under%20the%20Whistleblowers%20Protection%20Act%2C%202014%20in%20his%20latest%20letter%20which%20is%20also%20marked%20to%20the%20Principal%20Secretary%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20PMO%2C%20Cabinet%20Secretary%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Training%20and%20Chairman%2C%20IRDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20Yatish%20Yadav%2C%20the%20Media%20Advisor%20to%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%2C%20and%20also%20Chief%20Secretary%20Mehta%2C%20on%20the%20allegations%20of%20%E2%80%9Cabuse%20of%20official%20position%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20acts%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cconfer%20undue%20benefit%E2%80%9D%20on%20a%20private%20firm%20linked%20to%20Mehta.%20This%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20and%20when%20their%20responses%20are%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20top%20government%20official%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%20said%20the%20government%20will%20hold%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20spokesperson%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PM-JAY%20insurance%20scheme%20is%20fully%20funded%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20Ladakh%20while%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20local%20administration%20provides%2010%25%20funding%20support%20while%20the%20rest%20is%20borne%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Parmar%E2%80%99s%20letter%2C%20the%20State%20Health%20Agency%20(SHA)%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20Bajaj%20Allianz%20signed%20the%20three-year%20contract%20on%20December%2025%2C%202020%2C%20with%20a%20provision%20of%20annual%20review%20after%20two%20years%2C%20according%20to%20official%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClause%209(A)%20of%20the%20contract%2C%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20three%20year%20term%20of%20this%20insurance%20contract%20is%20subject%20to%20renewal%20after%20two%20years%20for%20one%20more%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202021%2C%20less%20than%20a%20year%20after%20the%20contract%20came%20into%20force%2C%20Bajaj%20Allianz%20sought%20to%20withdraw%2C%20reportedly%20citing%20losses.%20A%20top%20official%20of%20the%20administration%2C%20who%20is%20privy%20to%20the%20matter%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20insurance%20company%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20contract%20unless%20the%20SHA%20agreed%20in%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20SHA%20never%20agreed%20to%20the%20plea%20in%20writing.%20Instead%2C%20it%20changed%20the%20contract%20into%20a%20full%20reimbursement%20contract%20on%20December%2025%2C%202021%20with%20a%20top%20up%20fee%20of%2015%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said%2C%20underlining%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20original%20contract%20happened%20as%20a%20part%20of%20tendering%20process%2C%20but%20the%20addendum%20was%20arbitrary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInsurance%20companies%20cannot%20claim%20that%20they%20are%20running%20into%20a%20loss%20due%20to%20a%20particular%20insurance%20policy%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%20as%20that%20is%20what%20insurance%20is%20all%20about.%20Diversification%20leads%20to%20its%20viability.%20These%20claims%20and%20the%20SHA%20agreement%20in%20this%20particular%20contract%20has%20no%20basis%20in%20the%20insurance%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20added%2C%20claiming%20that%20the%20number%20of%20families%20was%20also%20%E2%80%9Cincreased%20by%201%2C087%2C108%20to%20provide%20more%20financial%20benefit%E2%80%9D%20to%20Bajaj%20Allianz.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20alleged%20scam%20happened%20between%20December%202021%20and%20April%202022%2C%20as%20per%20the%20modified%20agreement%2C%20and%20it%20has%20caused%20losses%20worth%20more%20than%20Rs%20500%20crore%20to%20the%20state%20exchequer%2C%20according%20to%20Parmar%E2%80%99s%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20order%20(No.%2049-JK(GAD)%20of%202019%20Dated%3A%2019-11-2019)%2C%20fund%20authorisation%20in%20central%20and%20state%20schemes%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20having%20financial%20implication%20of%20more%20than%20Rs%2050%20crore%20need%20the%20approval%20of%20Chief%20Secretary%20Mehta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20notification%20dated%20January%209%2C%202020%2C%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20finance%20department%20states%20that%20projects%20above%20Rs%2020%20crore%20shall%20be%20green-lighted%20after%20the%20approval%20of%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Sinha.%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20the%20offices%20have%20to%20be%20in%20the%20loop%20on%20the%20matter.%20It%20is%20either%20pure%20incompetence%20or%20a%20criminal%20nexus%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20quoted%20above%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20top%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20official%2C%20rejecting%20the%20claims%20made%20by%20Parmar%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20CBI%2C%20said%20that%20the%20policy%20was%20modified%20midway%20because%20Bajaj%20Allianz%20%E2%80%9Crefused%20to%20renew%E2%80%9D%20the%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNew%20contract%20would%20have%20taken%20perhaps%20three%20more%20months%20to%20finalise.%20During%20the%20intermediate%20period%2C%20an%20arrangement%20was%20made%20by%20the%20Health%20department%20as%20per%20General%20Finance%20Rules%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said%2C%20asking%20not%20to%20be%20quoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20point%20to%20the%20rules%20under%20which%20the%20contract%20was%20modified%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20choice%20was%20between%20continuity%20of%20service%20or%20disruption.%20Calculations%20made%20by%20the%20health%20department%20show%20that%20the%20model%20they%20adopted%20(to%20provide%2015%25%20extra%20charge%20to%20Bajaj%20Allianz%20was%20least%20costly%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697096018000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12125951%2FF76OrBQbIAAaSSf.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanoj-sinha-jammu-kashmir-bajaj-allianze-pmjay%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ashok%20Kumar%20Parmar%20has%20written%20to%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigations%20seeking%20a%20'deeper%20probe'%20by%20the%20Insurance%20Regulatory%20and%20Development%20Authority%20of%20India%20and%20the%20CBI%20into%20the%20matter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanoj-sinha-jammu-kashmir-bajaj-allianze-pmjay%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Licence%20of%20Company%20Whose%20Cough%20Syrups%20Were%20Linked%20to%20Deaths%20of%20Uzbek%20Kids%20Remains%20Cancelled%3A%20Officials%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F25160810%2Fpexels-cottonbro-studio-5858832.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20officials%20associated%20with%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20state%20drug%20control%20administration%20say%20the%20manufacturing%20licence%20of%20Marion%20Biotech%2C%20a%20Noida-based%20pharma%20firm%20whose%20cough%20syrup%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20deaths%20of%20more%20than%2060%20children%20in%20Uzbekistan%20last%20year%2C%20continues%20to%20remain%20cancelled%20as%20of%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20licence%20of%20the%20company%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fuzbekistan-cough-syrup-noida-marion-biotech-mandaviya%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecancelled%20on%20December%2030%2C%202022%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20Indian%20authorities%20as%20the%20Uzbekistan%20government%20found%20that%20Marion%20Biotech%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%20samples%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-uzbekistan-cough-syrup-noida-product-alert%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Dok1%20Max%20syrup%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Ambronol%20cough%20syrup%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20were%20contaminated%20with%20diethylene%20glycol%20(DEG)%20%E2%80%93%20an%20industrial%20solvent%20that%20is%20used%20as%20an%20antifreeze%20agent.%20According%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews%2Fitem%2F23-01-2023-who-urges-action-to-protect-children-from-contaminated-medicines%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWorld%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20can%20be%20fatal%20even%20if%20consumed%20in%20small%20amounts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20late%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2011%2C%20Noida%20drug%20inspector%20Vaibhav%20Babbar%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20company%E2%80%99s%20plant%20is%20not%20opened%20yet%20as%20the%20%5Blicence%5D%20cancellation%20order%20prevails.%E2%80%9D%20Asked%20again%2C%20he%20reiterated%20that%20the%20order%20%E2%80%9Csustains%20as%20of%20now%20and%20there%20is%20no%20ambiguity%20in%20that%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20further%20information%2C%20he%20redirected%20this%20correspondent%20to%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20head%20of%20drug%20control%20administration%2C%20Shashi%20Mohan%20Gupta.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGupta%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20company%20has%20not%20even%20submitted%20the%20corrective%20and%20preventive%20actions%20(CAPA)%20plan.%20So%20how%20can%20we%20even%20think%20of%20deliberating%20on%20revoking%20the%20cancellation%20order%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findia-allows-cough-syrup-firm-linked-uzbek-deaths-re-open-factory-document-2023-10-11%2F%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20on%20September%2014%2C%20Gupta%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20known%20case%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20quality%20in%20other%20medicines%20manufactured%20by%20the%20firm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20in%20view%20of%20natural%20justice%2C%20the%20appeal%20of%20the%20manufacturing%20firm%20is%20partially%20accepted.%20Its%20permission%20to%20make%20products%20using%20(cough%20syrup%20ingredient)%20propylene%20glycol%20is%20cancelled%2C%20and%20it%20is%20allowed%20to%20make%20and%20sell%20all%20other%20products%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reuters%20quoted%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20September%20statement%20as%20saying%2C%20on%20October%2011.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Findia-drug-impurities-fight%5C%22%3EInside%20the%20Fight%20To%20Decide%20How%20Pure%20India%E2%80%99s%20Drugs%20Need%20To%20Be%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20talking%20to%20The%20Wire%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20he%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20statement%2C%20but%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20licence%20of%20the%20entire%20plant%20remains%20cancelled%20%5Band%20as%20such%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20manufacture%20%3Cem%3Eany%3C%2Fem%3E%20drug%5D%20and%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20deliberated%20anything%20upon%20its%20reopening%20since%20the%20CAPA%20plan%20has%20not%20been%20submitted%20by%20the%20company%2C%20yet.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20CAPA%20plan%20is%20sent%20%5Bto%20us%5D%2C%20it%20would%20be%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Drug%20Controller%20General%20of%20India%2C%20Rajeev%20Raghuvanshi%2C%20for%20evaluation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%20Gupta%20also%20told%20Reuters%20on%20October%2011%20that%20Raghuvanshi%20had%20asked%20the%20company%20to%20submit%20the%20said%20plan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECAPA%20is%20a%20set%20of%20guidelines%20that%20a%20pharma%20firm%20commits%20to%20following%20once%20it%20has%20been%20found%20violating%20good%20manufacturing%20practices%20in%20an%20investigation%20carried%20out%20by%20drug%20regulatory%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20said%20plan%2C%20the%20company%20lists%20out%20the%20series%20of%20steps%20it%20would%20undertake%20to%20avoid%20repeating%20the%20violations.%20Once%20the%20plan%20is%20submitted%20to%20the%20regulatory%20authorities%2C%20they%20evaluate%20it%20and%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20its%20suitability%2C%20accordingly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20in%20March%202023%2C%20three%20people%20associated%20with%20the%20firm%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fuzbekistan-child-deaths-three-of-noida-based-firm-arrested-for-contaminated-medicines%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Earrested%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eby%20the%20Noida%20police%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20investigation%20done%20by%20drug%20control%20authorities.%20Marion%20Biotech%E2%80%99s%20owner%20was%20also%20named%20in%20the%20FIR.%20Asked%20about%20his%20status%2C%20the%20UP%20drug%20controller%20said%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20far%20as%20my%C2%A0%20limited%20knowledge%20goes%2C%20he%20got%20a%20stay%20%5Bon%20arrest%5D%20from%20a%20court.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20may%20be%20mentioned%20here%20that%20while%20the%20WHO%20had%20linked%20drugs%20of%20several%20companies%20based%20in%20India%20with%20deaths%20of%20children%20due%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20DEG%20in%20their%20respective%20products%2C%20it%20was%20only%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Marion%20Biotech%20that%20the%20government%20of%20India%20was%20also%20able%20to%20establish%20the%20contamination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20lab%20investigations.%20In%20no%20other%20such%20instance%20did%20the%20investigation%20in%20India%20establish%20the%20contamination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwith-officials-rarely-checking-for-impurities-indias-drug-testing-has-a-big-blind-spot%5C%22%3EWith%20Officials%20Rarely%20Checking%20for%20Impurities%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Drug%20Testing%20Has%20a%20Big%20Blind%20Spot%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUsually%2C%20DEG%20ends%20up%20entering%20these%20drugs%20through%20an%20ingredient%20called%20propylene%20glycol%20(PG)%2C%20which%20is%20added%20to%20syrups%20to%20make%20them%20soluble.%20However%2C%20either%20due%20to%20oversight%2C%20or%20to%20cut%20costs%2C%20pharma%20companies%20end%20up%20using%20PG-mixed%20DG.%20In%20case%20of%20oversight%2C%20they%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20test%20PG%20for%20any%20impurities%2C%20before%20production%20%E2%80%93%20which%20they%20are%20supposed%20to.%20In%20an%20earlier%20instance%2C%20Marion%20Biotech%E2%80%99s%20Tuhin%20Bhattacharya%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fhealth-coughsyrup-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EReuters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20his%20firms%20had%20sold%20drugs%20without%20checking%20PG%20for%20impurities%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697095773000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F25160810%2Fpexels-cottonbro-studio-5858832.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fmarion-biotech-licence-cough-syrup-uzbek-kids-remains-cancelled%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20report%20had%20said%20that%20barring%20cough%20syrups%2C%20Marion%20Biotech%20would%20be%20allowed%20to%20manufacture%20other%20products%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0provided%20it%20submitted%20the%20corrective%20and%20preventive%20actions%20plan.%20The%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20state%20drug%20controller%20told%20The%20Wire%20that%20the%20company%20has%20not%20yet%20submitted%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fmarion-biotech-licence-cough-syrup-uzbek-kids-remains-cancelled%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rockets%20fired%20at%20Tel%20Aviv%20after%20Israeli%20strikes%20on%20Gaza%20'civilians'%3A%20Hamas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697095528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104364495%2Cimgsize-40208.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Frockets-fired-at-tel-aviv-after-israeli-strikes-on-gaza-civilians-hamas%2Farticleshow%2F104364003.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104364003.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHamas%20militants%20on%20Thursday%20fired%20a%20barrage%20of%20rockets%20at%20Tel%20Aviv%20in%20response%20to%20Israeli%20air%20strikes%20that%20targeted%20%26quot%3Bcivilians%26quot%3B%20in%20two%20Gaza%20refugee%20camps%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20group%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Frockets-fired-at-tel-aviv-after-israeli-strikes-on-gaza-civilians-hamas%2Farticleshow%2F104364003.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Frockets-fired-at-tel-aviv-after-israeli-strikes-on-gaza-civilians-hamas%2Famp_articleshow%2F104364003.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Frockets-fired-at-tel-aviv-after-israeli-strikes-on-gaza-civilians-hamas%2Famp_articleshow%2F104364003.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Woman%E2%80%99s%20Autonomy%20Over%20Body%20vs%20Right%20to%20Life%20of%20Unborn%20Child%3A%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Split%20Judgment%20Decoded%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12115952%2FCambios_en_una_adolescente.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20division%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20heard%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-seeks-recall-of-scs-order-permitting-married-woman-to-terminate-26-week-pregnancy%5C%22%3Eapplication%20for%20recall%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20October%2010%20order%20directing%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20of%20a%20married%20woman%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2011.%20The%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20put%20on%20record%20the%20split%20among%20the%20two%20judges%20on%20whether%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20seek%20termination%20of%20her%20pregnancy%20could%20be%20recognised%20in%20the%2027th%20week%20of%20gestation.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%20observed%20that%20her%20judicial%20conscience%20could%20not%20permit%20ending%20the%20life%20of%20the%20unborn%20child%2C%20whose%20delivery%20was%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20Medical%20Board%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%20was%20persuaded%20by%20the%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%2C%20who%20submitted%20that%20the%20bench%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20ought%20not%20to%20be%20concerned%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20child%2C%20if%20born%20alive%2C%20but%20should%20only%20decide%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20petitioner-mother%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20terminate%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20the%2027th%20week%20could%20be%20recognised.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20email%20sent%20by%20one%20of%20the%20doctors%20on%20the%20AIIMS%20Medical%20Board%20pointed%20out%20that%20if%20the%20pregnancy%20is%20to%20be%20terminated%20as%20ordered%20by%20the%20court%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20child%20might%20be%20born%20alive%2C%20but%20with%20the%20risk%20of%20severe%20physical%20or%20mental%20disability.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Justice%20Kohli%20expressed%20her%20disappointment%20that%20the%20doctor%20concerned%20did%20not%20share%20her%20opinion%20ahead%20of%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20Tuesday%20order%20directing%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20she%20was%20inclined%20to%20consider%20it%20in%20order%20to%20recall%20that%20order%2C%20as%20sought%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20led%20the%20bench%20to%20talk%20afresh%20to%20the%20petitioner-woman%2C%20who%20was%20present%20in%20the%20court%20during%20the%20hearing%20on%20Wednesday.%20Although%20she%20had%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20saying%20she%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20continue%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20the%20bench%20confronted%20her%20with%20the%20doctor%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20and%20sought%20to%20know%20whether%20she%20could%20carry%20the%20pregnancy%20for%20one%20or%20two%20more%20weeks%2C%20if%20it%20ensured%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20her%20husband%20was%20agreeable%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20pregnancy%20for%20one%20or%20two%20more%20weeks%20as%20recommended%20by%20the%20doctor%2C%20the%20petitioner-woman%20clearly%20refused%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20this%20convinced%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20that%20her%20right%20over%20her%20body%20must%20be%20respected%20at%20all%20costs.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBhati%2C%20however%2C%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20bodily%20autonomy%20ends%20the%20moment%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child%20is%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20doctors.%20She%20also%20disclosed%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20readiness%20to%20take%20the%20responsibility%20of%20rearing%20the%20child%2C%20as%20the%20petitioner-mother%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20do%20so%20because%20of%20the%20limitations%20of%20her%20mental%20health%20and%20of%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20financial%20means%20to%20support%20another%20child.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20woman%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20she%20was%20suffering%20from%20lactational%20amenorrhea%20(which%20causes%20a%20temporary%20absence%20of%20menstruation%20in%20lactating%20mothers)%20and%20post-partum%20depression%20(a%20medical%20condition%20that%20many%20women%20experience%20after%20having%20a%20baby%2C%20with%20feelings%20of%20sadness%2C%20anxiety%20and%20tiredness).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20to%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20unwillingness%20to%20continue%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20even%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20state%20coming%20forward%20to%20rear%20the%20child%20through%20its%20adoption%20agency.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20while%20Justice%20Kohli%20accepted%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20recall%20application%20of%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20previous%20order%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20dismissed%20it.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%20also%20expressed%20her%20disappointment%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20mentioned%20the%20recall%20application%20before%20the%20bench%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20after%20the%20hearing%20in%20his%20court%20was%20over%20at%204%20pm%20on%20Tuesday.%20She%20termed%20it%20as%20an%20intra-court%20appeal%2C%20which%20could%20set%20a%20poor%20legal%20precedent%20within%20the%20court.%20Bhati%2C%20however%2C%20apologised%20for%20her%20conduct%2C%20as%20she%20claimed%20she%20could%20not%20mention%20it%20before%20the%20same%20bench%20on%20Tuesday%20because%20she%20was%20arguing%20another%20case%20before%20another%20bench.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20immediate%20precedent%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20delay%20caused%20by%20Wednesday%E2%80%99s%20split%20among%20the%20judges%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20of%20concern%20to%20the%20petitioner%2C%20the%20immediate%20precedent%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20court%20in%20another%20case%20could%20have%20been%20followed%20by%20the%20Kohli-Nagarathna%20bench%20in%20this%20case%20as%20well.%20But%20that%20was%20not%20considered%20during%20the%20hearing.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F680-xyz-v-state-of-gujarat-21-aug-2023-490042.pdf%5C%22%3EXYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Ethe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20had%20on%20August%2021%20held%20that%20a%20woman%20alone%20has%20the%20right%20over%20her%20body%20and%20is%20the%20ultimate%20decision-maker%20on%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20she%20wants%20to%20undergo%20an%20abortion.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20report%20of%20the%20medical%20board%2C%20constituted%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%2C%20had%20stated%20that%20although%20there%20is%20no%20congenital%20abnormality%20in%20the%20foetus%2C%20the%20medical%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20could%20only%20be%20done%20if%20the%20court%20permits%2C%20after%20taking%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20appellant%20and%20explaining%20potential%20risk%20to%20maternal%20health.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20rape%20survivor%20in%20this%20case%20was%20clinically%20fit%20for%20the%20termination%20procedure%20and%20the%20MTP%20would%20not%20adversely%20affect%20child-bearing%20capacity%20and%20her%20general%20health%20in%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20in%3Ci%3E%C2%A0XYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20the%20age%20of%20the%20foetus%20was%20almost%2027%20weeks%20when%20the%20court%20examined%20the%20plea%20for%20termination%20of%20pregnancy.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgain%20as%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20adverse%20impact%20of%20the%20continuance%20of%20the%20pregnancy%20on%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20mental%20health%20was%20considered%20a%20relevant%20factor%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20may%20be%20argued%20that%20in%20%3Cem%3EXYZ%20vs%20State%20of%20Gujarat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20adverse%20impact%20on%20the%20mental%20health%20of%20the%20mother%20was%20anticipated%20because%20she%20was%20a%20rape%20survivor%20and%20the%20court%20considered%20the%20resultant%20trauma.%20In%20the%20present%20case%2C%20however%2C%20to%20Justice%20Nagarathna%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20petitioner%20is%20a%20married%20woman%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20case%20of%20voluntary%20pregnancy%2C%20did%20not%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20conclusion%20that%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20of%20adverse%20impact%20on%20her%20mental%20health%20if%20the%20pregnancy%20continued%20beyond%2027%20weeks.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Kohli%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20was%20persuaded%20by%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20contention%20that%20permitting%20the%20MTP%20of%20a%20married%20woman%20beyond%2027%20weeks%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20delivery%20of%20a%20healthy%20child%20is%20found%20viable%20by%20the%20doctors%20%E2%80%93%20may%20set%20a%20wrong%20precedent%20and%20that%20there%20may%20be%20others%20who%20could%20exploit%20it%20and%20seek%20MTP%20beyond%2027%20weeks%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20the%20mother%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20health%20concerns%E2%80%9D%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20possibility%20of%20giving%20away%20the%20child%20for%20adoption.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20the%20new%20bench%20would%20deal%20with%20these%20delicate%20issues%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20watch.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697094949000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12115952%2FCambios_en_una_adolescente.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwoman-autonomy-body-vs-right-to-life-unborn-child-supreme-court-split-judgment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20split%20on%20a%20married%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20abort%20her%20pregnancy%20in%20the%2027th%20week%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20the%20CJI%20to%20constitute%20another%20bench%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwoman-autonomy-body-vs-right-to-life-unborn-child-supreme-court-split-judgment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Global%20Leadership%20Is%20Not%20Just%20About%20Drafting%20a%20Statement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22165508%2FH20230909138364.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20not%20attending%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20party%20at%20the%20G-20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20effectively%20signalled%20that%20the%20group%20no%20longer%20matters%20in%20geo-economic%20and%20geo-political%20terms.%20What%20matters%20is%20the%20G-7%20and%20its%20direct%20competitor%20BRICS.%20And%20if%20the%20South%20African%20edition%20of%20BRICS%20is%20the%20sign%20of%20times%20to%20come%2C%20then%20this%20is%20where%20the%20world%20is%20converging.%20However%2C%20to%20convey%20China%E2%80%99s%20core%20message%