an.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2011%2C%20reiterated%20its%20recommendation%20to%20transfer%20Justice%20M.V.%20Muralidharan%20from%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%20to%20Calcutta%2C%20saying%20the%20decision%20was%20taken%20for%20%E2%80%9Cbetter%20administration%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20collegium%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20proposed%20the%20transfer%20on%20October%209%2C%20but%20on%20the%20next%20day%2C%C2%A0Justice%20Muralidharan%20requested%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20his%20parent%20high%20court%20(Madras)%20or%20continue%20at%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20considered%20the%20requests%20made%20by%20Mr%20Justice%20Muralidharan%20in%20his%20above%20communication.%20The%20Collegium%20does%20not%20find%20merit%20in%20the%20requests%20made%20by%20him.%20The%20Collegium%2C%20therefore%2C%20resolves%20to%20reiterate%20its%20October%209%2C%202023%20recommendation%20to%20transfer%20Mr%20Justice%20Muralidharan%20to%20the%20High%20Court%20at%20Calcutta%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FCollegium%2F11102023_070542.pdf%5C%22%3Enote%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20collegium%20on%20Wednesday%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20collegium%20said%20as%20per%20the%20memorandum%20of%20procedure%2C%20it%20had%20consulted%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20who%20is%20conversant%20with%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20Manipur%20HC%20and%20spoke%20to%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Calcutta%20HC%20before%20recommending%20Justice%20Muralidharan%E2%80%99s%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Muralidharan%20is%20the%20acting%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%2C%20a%20role%20he%20has%20been%20performing%20since%20Justice%20P.V.%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20was%20elevated%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20February%202023.%20While%20